One of the most important takeaways for me was understanding that using the right keywords from the job description is crucial for getting past the ATS. If your r√©sum√© doesn‚Äôt match the language in the job listing, it could get filtered out before a recruiter even sees it. Another key point was keeping my r√©sum√© formatting simple‚Äîno fancy fonts, tables, or graphics. These tips are definitely going to give me an edge in today‚Äôs competitive job market. Another key point was keeping my r√©sum√© formatting simple‚Äîno fancy fonts, tables, or graphics. Casey Miller‚Äôs session on ATS was incredibly eye-opening for me as a business major! I never realized how small formatting details could make such a big difference in whether my r√©sum√© gets noticed. One of the most important takeaways for me was understanding that using the right keywords from the job description is crucial for getting past the ATS. If your r√©sum√© doesn‚Äôt match the language in the job listing, it could get filtered out before a recruiter even sees it. Another key point was keeping my r√©sum√© formatting simple‚Äîno fancy fonts, tables, or graphics. The ATS reads best when sections are clear and straightforward, and using bullet points helps highlight key skills in an easy-to-scan way. These tips are definitely going to give me an edge in today‚Äôs competitive job market. *Cue Anxiety by Doechii*The reality of job searching is that there are moments, days, or even weeks when you‚Äôre riddled with anxiety. Anxiety regarding:  Hearing back  Getting an interview Doing well on the interview  Dealing with ghosting Telling yourself the rejections are not personal  Not receiving any feedback  The endless rounds of interviews  Tailoring your resume for the 100th time  Dodging scammers Sifting through shell job listingsThis list is not comprehensive by any means. I am not here to rehash the traumas of job hunting but want to remind everyone that eventually every flower has to bloom. I have been seen the green banners coming down and people landing more interviews as the weeks progress and it‚Äôs refreshing to see. There were moments when all I saw on my timeline was desperation and frustration- both feelings are valid in this market but they are also counterproductive. The sun is starting to shine in the East Coast and I‚Äôve been making it my business to sit outside and soak in some vitamin D. I started journaling to organize my thoughts and plan out my moves. Anxiety leaves you in a vicious cycle of insecurity, desperation, fear, and despair. These times are tough but you‚Äôre tougher! I see the struggle and am sitting in it but I know it will all come together how it needs to.  My faith has not dimmed. hashtag#OpenToConnect hashtag#Anxiety hashtag#KeepGoing hashtag#GrowthMindset

*Cue Anxiety by Doechii*The reality of job searching is that there are moments, days, or even weeks when you‚Äôre riddled with anxiety. Anxiety regarding:  Hearing back  Getting an interview Doing well on the interview  Dealing with ghosting Telling yourself the rejections are not personal  Not receiving any feedback  The endless rounds of interviews  Tailoring your resume for the 100th time  Dodging scammers Sifting through shell job listingsThis list is not comprehensive by any means. I am not here to rehash the traumas of job hunting but want to remind everyone that eventually every flower has to bloom. I have been seen the green banners coming down and people landing more interviews as the weeks progress and it‚Äôs refreshing to see. There were moments when all I saw on my timeline was desperation and frustration- both feelings are valid in this market but they are also counterproductive. The sun is starting to shine in the East Coast and I‚Äôve been making it my business to sit outside and soak in some vitamin D. I started journaling to organize my thoughts and plan out my moves. Anxiety leaves you in a vicious cycle of insecurity, desperation, fear, and despair. These times are tough but you‚Äôre tougher! I see the struggle and am sitting in it but I know it will all come together how it needs to.  My faith has not dimmed. hashtag#OpenToConnect hashtag#Anxiety hashtag#KeepGoing hashtag#GrowthMindset
